The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Damages

 New Delhi, Oct. 10: The National Human Rights Commission today directed the Punjab government to award a compensation of Rs 1.75 lakh to the next of kin of 1,051 people who were unceremoniously cremated and not given honorable farewell by state authorities during the militancy.




